# No Single-Use Function Extractions

Do not extract a helper function whose only purpose is to be called once. It adds indirection without value. Inline the logic at the call site instead.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — buildInput is called exactly once; the abstraction is pointless
const buildInput = (prompt: string): Record<string, unknown> => {
  return { prompt, system_prompt: SYSTEM_PROMPT }
}

export const generateComment = async (prompt: string): Promise<string> => {
  const output = await model.run({ input: buildInput(prompt) })
  return parse(output)
}

// ✅ GOOD — logic lives directly where it is used
export const generateComment = async (prompt: string): Promise<string> => {
  const output = await model.run({ input: { prompt, system_prompt: SYSTEM_PROMPT } })
  // ... parse output
}
```

A function is worth extracting only when it is called from **two or more** distinct call sites, or when it has a meaningful name that replaces a non-obvious comment.
